author: pburba
msg: On the auto-props-sdc branch: Tweak caching of auto-props during 'svn add'
when the target is an already versioned directory with unversioned subtrees
eligible for addition.
Fixes schedule_tests.py 11 "'svn add' should traverse already-versioned
dirs" and
* subversion/libsvn_client/add.c
(add_file): Handle the case where the caller doesn't send any auto-props
and we need to get them ourselves.  Also delay getting autoprops until we
know the file isn't already versioned.
(add_dir_recursive): Handle the case where the caller doesn't send any
auto-props and we need to get them ourselves.  Use the two-pool paradigm,
which isn't absolutely necessary right now, but is much clearer.
(find_existing_parent): Define before new first caller.
(svn_client__get_all_auto_props): Don't assume target is always versioned;
support the case where the target is the root of an unversioned subtree.
(add): Stop getting autoprops, wait till our recursive callees encounter
the root of an unversioned subtree, because different subtrees may
inherit different svn:config:auto-props.
* subversion/libsvn_client/client.h
(svn_client__get_paths_auto_props): Some whitespace formatting changes.
(svn_client__get_all_auto_props): Describe new behavior and some whitespace
formatting.
* subversion/tests/cmdline/autoprop_tests.py
(inheritable_autoprops_test): Return the location of the config dir used
for the test.  Also remove some development/testing cruft.
(svn_config_autoprops_add_versioned_target): Remove XFail decorator and
related commentary.  Adjust execution of 'svn add' so that it uses the
correct --config-dir target and targets the WC so as to avoid a spurious
error.
